        <div class="msgSubject">Is it possible to play on a Mac?</div>
        <div class="sm notbold">
          
          Posted: 2010-11-18 14:08:34   | <input type="checkbox" name="quote-1290110914265382164" id="quote-1290110914265382164" class="msgQuoteCheck" onchange="multiQuote2()"/><label for="quote-1290110914265382164" onclick="multiQuote2()"> Quote</label>  | <a href="/forum.html?forum=10&amp;mid=1290110914265382164&amp;post=1&amp;replyto=1290110914265382164&amp;page=1" class="icon-replytothis" rel="nofollow">Reply to Post</a> | <a id="FOLLOW_MID_1290110914265382164" onclick="followToggle('add','1290110914265382164')" href="javascript:" class="icon-follow">Follow</a> 
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgWhoFrame">
        <div class="msgUM"><a class="msgWhoName Sage" href="/users/Courtelise">Courtelise</a><div class="msgWhoTitle Sage">Sage</div></div><div class="msgAvatar"></div><div class="msgStar"><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/><img src="http://common.zam.com/shared/s2.gif" alt="*"/></div><div class="msgWhoNum">617 posts</div>
        <div class="msgScore">
          Score: Good  
          <div class="msgRatings"></div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="msgContentFrame">Short version of the story: my laptop suffered severe hardware failure and while I can still play on my old laptop, I'm in the market for a shiny new one.  Since I can't seem to keep a Windows based machine alive for more than 2-3 years, it was suggested I buy a Mac. <br /> <br />Now, I know I can run a virtual windows machine on my mac, and assuming it meets minimum specs, I &quot;should&quot; be able to play windows based games.  Meanwhile I'd have the Mac end for my work (self employed) and hopefully a more hardy machine that will last longer than 3 years.  Frequent travel requires I purchase a laptop as opposed to a desktop. <br /> <br />Any real life stories of doing something like this? <br /> <br />Assuming it is possible, I can say with reasonable certainty that overtaxing the graphics card and the resulting heat being generated played an important role in my graphics card's doom.  I have to change out the whole mobo in order to fix it and I'm not sure it's worth it. <br /> <br />Looking at pics online of macs, I'm wondering if they have the cooling power required for intense gaming. <br /> <br />Thoughts? <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Courtelise <br />AION - 42 Spiritmaster <br />Server: Azphel  <br />FFXI - 75 RDM/63 BST <br />Server: Fairy (RIP)-&gt;Sylph</div></div>
