      <div class="msgContentFrame">I haven't found &quot;good&quot; yet when it comes to laptops.   <br /> <br />I come from a design background, so of course all of my people there are pushing Mac as the most robust... ie: still going strong after 4+ years.  Then again, they don't abuse graphics cards the way I do. <br /> <br />Any recommendations from my fellow gamers? <br /> <br />Edit just to clarify: Good = can withstand gaming and the ability to upgrade as required.  My first laptop, a Dell, is still running, but the internal network card fried within a year.  My second, a Gateway, did well until now.. after 2.5 years, I fried the graphics card.  I can live with that if only it were easily replaced. <br /> <br /><i><span class="sm">Edited, Nov 18th 2010  3:27pm by Courtelise </span></i><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Courtelise <br />AION - 42 Spiritmaster <br />Server: Azphel  <br />FFXI - 75 RDM/63 BST <br />Server: Fairy (RIP)-&gt;Sylph</div></div>
