      <div class="msgContentFrame">Chew beat me to the upgrade aspect of laptops. As for Dell, the only real knock I have on them is their pricing. My old PC from them is 9 years old now and still running, practically kept on 24/7 except for random power outages or times I popped the case to put in a better video card, more RAM, a bigger HD, or to clean some dust out. My folks have been using it as their main PC now, also leaving it on 24/7. My only real regret with it was not knowing the difference between RAM types at the time. RDRAM = Hella Expensive, and compounded by the fact you need to buy two sticks at a time to effectively upgrade.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div><a href="HTTP://home.comcast.net/~clg2001/KeanuRDM.gif" rel="external nofollow" title="home.comcast.net/~clg2001/KeanuRDM.gif">06/21/2010: Keanu represents RDMs everywhere.</a></div></div>
