      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Grand Master Leatherworker ThePsychoticO wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Delsinax wrote:</div><div class="orig">tl;dr: Yes, you can run FFXI on windows.</div></div>ftfy <br /> <br />If you're just going to be running it in windows anyway, why did you pay so much for that logo on the back? Oh, same reason people buy macs anyway: for the logo.</div></div> <br /> <br />Fair enough - you can run FFXI on Mac hardware using Windows. <br /> <br />Incidentally, I agree it's silly to buy anything for the logo.  I bought my Mac because every person I knew with a Windows-based laptop complained about the OS, including myself, and those laptops seem to have hardware failures and incompatibilities reasonably often (meaning more often than &quot;never to almost never&quot;, which is what I expect from an expensive piece of equipment like a laptop).  My Mac has been very reliable.  The only reason I run Windows is to play FFXI (I would have waited to buy Civ 5 if I didn't have Windows already installed). <br /> <br />Come to think of it, the only Apple logo I can even see when I'm using the computer is the Apple menu in the upper left corner.  Buying this computer just for that would have been a poor choice indeed.</div>
