      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Grand Master Leatherworker ThePsychoticO wrote:</div><div class="orig"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Delsinax wrote:</div><div class="orig">and writing skills, as any high school graduate such as yourself should know the proper contraction for &quot;you are&quot;).</div></div>I don't know why i do that so often [:frown:] <br /> <br />If you don't have extra money to spend, then why exactly are you throwing it away to buy something that you could get for half the price, without the logo?</div></div> <br /> <br />I thought I mentioned that earlier.  I have found Macs to be more reliable then PC systems, and I prefer MacOS to Windows.  It's much less annoying to configure things.  Although tweaking options away from default can sometimes be an interesting challenge, it's doable, and the default options work very well for most things; Windows systems I've owned and interacted with always seem to be at least one configuration tweak away from doing what I actually want it to do. <br /> <br />Oh, and I really like showing off the big logo on the back.  Sorry, couldn't help myself.  ;) <br /> <br />Seriously, I got tired of spending more and more money replacing parts on my Thinkpad which always seemed to blow up about a week after they went out of warranty, while being unable to get drivers to work properly and applications to run the way they should.  Maybe that computer was just cursed.  I'm not the most technically savvy person out here - I haven't managed to do anything more complicated than set up a Red Hat server on an old Linux box to distribute the DSL back in grad school - but I promise I've never been that guy who doesn't even know how to plug something in and turn it on.  My Mac works, all of my friends with Macs don't have complaints about them, and I've been happy with it.  I know plenty of folks who are happy with Windows machines, too.  As I've mentioned a few times, I can see good reasons for buying either. <br /> <br />Thanks for the chat.  It's been fun, and it's done wonders for my post count.  :P</div>
