      <div class="msgContentFrame">Here is a post from someone who knows very little about computers and has not owned a desk top in 10 years.  <br /> <br />No real gamer buys Apple laptops, for one reason and one reason only, you can buy the same exact laptop for 1/2 to 1/3 the price, considering that any avid gamer has to update laptops every three years anyway, why the hell would you pay an extra thousand bucks every three years. Makes no sense. And if your telling me your three year old laptop can play the latest and greatest games your full of it.  <br /> <br />Now I have noticed that my non-gamer friends get more bang for their buck out of owning an apple simply because they have considerably less problems with viruses, so maybe if all you play is FFXI and you have no intention of playing any other game, go ahead.  <br /> <br />With regard to Dell, I have been shopping around for a new laptop for a while, going to pull the trigger soon.  For laptops over 1,200 I have not found a Dell laptop that is not at least 20% more expensive then a similarly equiped Toshiba, HP or any major brand.  Although they are tough to beat at the 300-500 dollar range. <br /> <br /> <br /><div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div>Pld 85 War 88 Rdm 90 Drg 85 Cor 83 Blm 80 Smn 85 <br />Retired - Thf 75 Drk 75   <br /></div></div>
